"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">Header = attributes|weapons|spells|items</p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">Header Spec = &lt;plain text&gt;|stat modifier|randomizer|dice table</p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">plain text = Any plain text with possibly %d %e %s in them. If more then one line use &lt;&gt; to start and stop the text.</p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">%d = will be replaced with damage appropriate for creature based on things like the number of weapons and multi-attack. In order to have a sensable damage output for the creature of this level.</p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">%e = will be replaced with sensable elemental damage or status effect damage, which will be taken as 10% of %d. </p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">%s = will be replaced with the proficency bonus or Spell Save DC if specified as %s[STAT]</p>\n"
